Flying into Kathmandu is a thrill! The airport is surrounded by terrain and high mountains. The approach is steep, with fast changing weather into play. It is captain’s landing only. Watch how @gonationalair B747 cargo plane land there to bringing in medical aid supplies.

External footage by @flight_101_ @ktmspotter

2020 was no ordinary year, but it was definitely one to remember.
I have been recording and documenting Aviation’s response to COVID since day 1. The aviation industry has been so responsive to its survival.

.
.

Watch this spectacular flypass to celebrate @qantas 100th birthday! 
Sydney has commemorated Qantas 100-year anniversary by lighting up its iconic Sydney Harbour Bridge as a larger-than-life birthday cake complete with illuminated candles that were blown out by a Qantas 787 as it did a low level overfly at 1,500 feet.

More than 1,300 LED tubes, 126 LED fixtures and 38 searchlights lit up the full expanse of the world’s most famous bridge in the ultimate tribute from Sydney, the city which has been home to Qantas for more than eight decades.
 
200 passengers, including 100 Qantas staff, were on board the 100-minute flight which was a special Centenary Scenic Flight to mark the airline’s 100th year. ✈️ (Footage: Qantas)
.

What a beautiful cockpit and cabin!

The new @gulfstreamaero G700 boasts business aviation’s most spacious cabin and can fly farther, and faster than any other competitor in the business-jet industry. Powered by two Rolls-Royce Pearl 700 engines, the G700 can fly 7,500 nautical miles/13,890 kilometres at Mach 0.85. (Max speed Mach .925)

It features an amazing Symmetry Flight Deck with active control sidesticks and the most extensive use of touchscreen technology in the industry. G700 cockpit has done away with most buttons with a clean design.

@qatarexecutive is the launch customer of G700 and expect to take delivery next year.

This Saturday I will be taking you on a tour to experience the Gulfstream Flagship ✈️

New vlog is out on YouTube! (Full video link in my bio)

In September 2016, I traveled to North Korea to attend the country's first Air Show; Wonsan AirShow. It was the most exotic airshow I've ever attended!

The airshow was an unqualified smash hit, showing off North Korea’s aviation scene and bringing together foreign visitors and locals without hindrance for the first time in the country’s history.

In the video, I also shared what's it like to fly on Air Koryo's exotic fleet. From modern Tupolev 204 to vintage classic IL-18 , IL-62, IL-76 and Tu-154. It is definitely an exotic experience you don't want to miss!

node.text:
I’m deeply honored to receive the Golden Visa from the UAE 🇦🇪 

I have almost nothing when I came to the UAE 10 years ago. I knew very little about my future direction. It turned out the UAE is a country that changed my life! You’re all my witnessing my growth!

During my 10 years here, I am able to align my passion into my work to build up my aviation portfolio. The opportunities, connections, networking and diverse friendship from this key aviation hub here are just amazing!

Believe in yourself and follow your passion with strong determination! A small step at a time and never give up trying! “Your future is as bright as you want it to be!”

Special thanks to @filmdubai for supporting passionate people with their dreams! Also thanks to @gdrfadubai and @dubaimediaoffice

Unbelievable (heartbreaking) scenes at Kabul Airport today as many hang on to the landing gear of C-17 in a desperate attempt to leave the country. (Sadly few fell out of the sky as the plane tookoff)

The civilian side of Kabul airport is now closed and airspace handed to the military. Plenty of rescue flights are planned. More info are on my blog SamChui.com

Video via Twitter/Babak Taghvaee
